11 APRIL. 8 WILL. ΠΙ. 1696.

This is the final agreement made in the court of the Lord the King of his great session of the oounty of GLAMORGAN held at CARDIFF in the eounty aforesaid on Saturday the eleventh day of April in the eighth year of the reign of the Lord W1LL1AM the Third after the Gonquest King of ENGLAND ScoTLAND FRANCE and IRELAND Defender of the Faith &a Before WILLIAM PovaETT Serjeant-at-law and EDWARD SMYTH esquire justioes and other faithful people of the Lord the King then there present Between RoGER WILLIAMS gentleman plaintiff and ΤΗοΜΑο GRIFFITH gentleman and ELIZABETH his wife deforciants of one messuage one barn one garden ten aeres of land thirty aeres of meadow twenty aeres of pastnre and a hundred and twenty aeres of furze and heath with appurtenanoes in the parish of YSTRADYVODUCK whereof a plea of oovenant was summoned between them in the same court to wit that the aforesaid THOMAS and ELIZABETH aoknowledged the tenements aforesaid with appurtenanoes to be the right of the same ROGER as those which the same Roman has of the gift of the aforesaid THOMAs and ELIZABETH And those they have remised and quitolaimed for themselves and the heirs of the same THOMAs to the aforenamed ROGER and his heirs for ever And moreover the same THOMAs and ELIZABETH have granted for themselves and the heirs of the same THOMAS that they will warrant the tenements aforesaid with appurtenanoes to the aforenamed ROGER and his heirs against all men for ever And for this aoknowledgment remise quitolaim
